WEBVTT

00:01.002 --> 00:06.572
<i> ♪ [dramatic music] ♪</i>

00:06.674 --> 00:07.540
Ahem!

00:08.242 --> 00:11.710
I don't want to tattle
on my good friend, Tirek,

00:11.812 --> 00:16.081
but.. you might like to know
he left food out. Again.

00:16.183 --> 00:18.050
I'll deal with it when I'm done.

00:18.352 --> 00:20.852
♪♪

00:20.954 --> 00:24.957
Don't trust anything that
nosy little Pegasus says.

00:25.059 --> 00:27.926
I don't trust anything
any of you say.

00:28.228 --> 00:28.996
Hmph.

00:30.898 --> 00:32.832
Are you planning on
attacking anypony

00:32.934 --> 00:35.534
anytime soon? If
not, I don't know why

00:35.636 --> 00:39.338
I'm wasting my time here.
I am a <i>queen</i>, you know!

00:41.609 --> 00:44.843
I am leaving, since it's
impossible to accomplish

00:44.945 --> 00:46.678
the work I need to do here!

00:46.880 --> 00:50.515
I suggest the three of you
come to some kind of accord.

00:53.554 --> 00:58.157
I don't care how, but you
must learn to work together!

00:58.259 --> 01:01.760
Only then can we accomplish
what you so greatly desire:

01:01.962 --> 01:06.198
the defeat of Twilight
Sparkle and her friends!

01:44.805 --> 01:51.510
♪♪

01:51.812 --> 01:55.448
Nothing says teamwork like
an inspirational banner!

01:56.050 --> 01:57.716
When Grogar sees this,

01:57.818 --> 02:00.886
he'll realize there's no way
he could survive without me!

02:05.526 --> 02:07.192
You're gonna have
to exercise a lot

02:07.294 --> 02:08.177
to get as big as you were

02:08.278 --> 02:10.461
when you absorbed the life
force of all those ponies.

02:11.849 --> 02:14.533
Anyhoo... Grogar wants
us all to work together

02:14.635 --> 02:16.302
so I've scheduled
a team meeting!

02:17.204 --> 02:19.004
Doesn't that sound <i>fun</i> !?

02:20.307 --> 02:23.308
And since Grogar
left <i>me</i> in charge...

02:23.410 --> 02:24.576
No, he didn't!

02:25.813 --> 02:28.414
Someone's a real
grumpy-taur today.

02:28.916 --> 02:31.450
If we aren't meeting, I
guess I could just stay

02:31.552 --> 02:33.519
and offer positive
and inspiring-

02:33.621 --> 02:36.955
Fine! I'll join your
meeting. Just leave.

02:37.057 --> 02:38.223
See you soon!

02:40.194 --> 02:43.262
It's been weeks and
Grogar has done nothing!

02:43.364 --> 02:46.198
It's not healthy to hold
onto all of this rage!

02:46.700 --> 02:48.667
I could lash out at any moment...

02:49.069 --> 02:50.769
And how are you
doing this fine...

02:50.871 --> 02:52.437
HOW DO YOU THINK I'M DOING!?

02:52.539 --> 02:54.706
I'm ready to exact my revenge!

02:55.108 --> 02:56.308
See what I mean?

02:56.610 --> 02:59.411
Being cooped up with
nothing to do is the worst.

02:59.513 --> 03:02.281
You know what you
need? A team meeting!

03:02.583 --> 03:04.650
I don't do meetings.

03:04.752 --> 03:06.785
Grogar left me in charge.

03:06.887 --> 03:11.523
No, he didn't! And even if he
did, Chrysalis obeys no one.

03:11.825 --> 03:13.292
There'll be cupcakes...

03:15.662 --> 03:17.362
Grogar wants us to work together

03:17.464 --> 03:18.764
to defeat our enemies.

03:18.866 --> 03:21.401
Which means we need
to trust each other.

03:22.403 --> 03:24.736
If we are to trust one another,

03:24.938 --> 03:27.406
perhaps inform Lord Tirek...

03:27.508 --> 03:30.275
to STOP trying to
absorb my essence!

03:31.779 --> 03:36.848
Pfft. I wasn't doing anything
of the sort! How dare you?

03:36.950 --> 03:40.986
How dare I? Do you know
to whom you are speaking?

03:42.790 --> 03:46.392
How could I not! You tell
your log every five minutes!

03:46.794 --> 03:49.194
This is why Grogar
left me in charge...!

03:49.296 --> 03:51.763
NO! HE! DIDN'T!

03:52.365 --> 03:53.632
♪♪

03:53.734 --> 03:55.333
Grrrr!  ...Huh?

03:55.435 --> 04:01.973
♪♪

04:02.075 --> 04:03.775
<i> ♪ I think I know ♪</i>

04:03.877 --> 04:05.377
<i> ♪ A way that we can grow ♪</i>

04:05.479 --> 04:09.114
<i> ♪ Time to try something</i>
<i> new something better ♪</i>

04:09.416 --> 04:11.082
<i> ♪ No more Solo ♪</i>

04:11.184 --> 04:12.884
<i> ♪ Trust is the way to go ♪</i>

04:12.986 --> 04:14.553
<i> ♪ And all we need to do ♪</i>

04:14.655 --> 04:17.155
<i> ♪ is work together ♪</i>

04:17.257 --> 04:18.457
Ah, please.

04:18.559 --> 04:20.125
<i> ♪ No, thanks. No way ♪</i>

04:20.327 --> 04:22.060
<i> ♪ I feel the need to say ♪</i>

04:22.162 --> 04:23.562
<i> ♪ I'm smarter, stronger and ♪</i>

04:23.664 --> 04:25.130
<i> ♪ I don't need you two. ♪</i>

04:25.232 --> 04:26.631
<i> ♪ Hah! Stronger? ♪</i>

04:26.733 --> 04:27.466
<i> ♪ OK. ♪</i>

04:27.568 --> 04:29.368
<i> ♪ I guess we'll downplay ♪</i>

04:29.470 --> 04:31.336
<i> ♪ How bad you got</i>
<i> your rear-end ♪</i>

04:31.438 --> 04:34.506
<i> ♪ Handed to you? ♪</i>

04:34.908 --> 04:36.141
<i> ♪ It's time to try ♪</i>

04:36.243 --> 04:38.243
<i> ♪ A better way to be bad ♪</i>

04:38.545 --> 04:39.811
<i> ♪ Do we really need ♪</i>

04:39.913 --> 04:42.113
<i> ♪ A better way to be bad? ♪</i>

04:42.215 --> 04:43.682
<i> ♪ United as one! ♪</i>

04:43.784 --> 04:45.650
<i> ♪ Teamwork? Please,</i>
<i> what a fad! ♪</i>

04:45.752 --> 04:47.452
<i> ♪ Combine all our strength ♪</i>

04:47.554 --> 04:49.054
<i> ♪ We'll go to any length ♪</i>

04:49.156 --> 04:50.073
<i> ♪ Once we have ♪</i>

04:50.174 --> 04:52.791
<i> ♪ A better way to be bad ♪</i>

04:54.862 --> 04:55.594
<i> ♪ Let's go! ♪</i>

04:55.796 --> 04:56.546
<i> ♪ Begin ♪</i>

04:56.647 --> 04:58.297
<i> ♪ This time we're gonna win! ♪</i>

04:58.399 --> 04:59.765
<i> ♪ The ice you're on is thin ♪</i>

04:59.867 --> 05:01.900
<i> ♪ So watch what you say ♪</i>

05:02.102 --> 05:02.968
<i> ♪ I know ♪</i>

05:03.070 --> 05:03.936
<i> ♪ You're in ♪</i>

05:04.037 --> 05:05.603
<i> ♪ I think I see a grin! ♪</i>

05:05.706 --> 05:07.138
<i> ♪ For all this pain</i>
<i> and torture ♪</i>

05:07.240 --> 05:10.042
<i> ♪ I swear you'll pay ♪</i>

05:10.344 --> 05:11.643
<i> ♪ This time we've got ♪</i>

05:11.745 --> 05:13.678
<i> ♪ A better way to be bad ♪</i>

05:13.980 --> 05:15.313
<i> ♪ Sounds like a long shot ♪</i>

05:15.415 --> 05:17.549
<i> ♪ This better way to be bad ♪</i>

05:17.651 --> 05:19.017
<i> ♪ United as one! ♪</i>

05:19.119 --> 05:21.352
<i> ♪ We'll make those ponies so</i>
<i> sad! ♪</i>

05:21.454 --> 05:22.821
<i> ♪ If we say OK ♪</i>

05:22.923 --> 05:24.623
<i> ♪ would you just go away? ♪</i>

05:24.725 --> 05:25.424
<i> ♪ Once we have ♪</i>

05:25.526 --> 05:28.527
<i> ♪ A better way to be bad! ♪</i>

05:28.629 --> 05:30.228
<i> ♪ We want to break</i>
<i> their friendship ♪</i>

05:30.330 --> 05:32.030
<i> ♪ We want to make them weak ♪</i>

05:32.132 --> 05:33.898
<i> ♪ You want revenge</i>
<i> on Starlight ♪</i>

05:34.000 --> 05:35.667
<i> ♪ You want that huge physique ♪</i>

05:35.769 --> 05:37.469
<i> ♪ So let's increase</i>
<i> our chances ♪</i>

05:37.571 --> 05:39.171
<i> ♪ By working as a team ♪</i>

05:39.273 --> 05:41.039
<i> ♪ To crush our</i>
<i> enemies to dust ♪</i>

05:41.141 --> 05:43.074
<i> ♪ And laugh as</i>
<i> they all scream! ♪</i>

05:44.911 --> 05:46.345
<i> ♪ I think I see ♪</i>

05:46.447 --> 05:48.613
<i> ♪ A better way to be bad ♪</i>

05:48.715 --> 05:49.881
<i> ♪ Just put me in charge! ♪</i>

05:49.983 --> 05:51.016
<i> ♪ Make me Queen; ♪</i>

05:51.118 --> 05:51.917
<i> ♪ you'll be glad ♪</i>

05:52.019 --> 05:53.618
<i> ♪ No! Listen to me! ♪</i>

05:53.720 --> 05:55.420
<i> ♪ I'm the best of us three ♪</i>

05:55.522 --> 05:56.188
<i> ♪ Then you'll see ♪</i>

05:56.290 --> 05:59.190
<i> ♪ A better way to be bad ♪</i>

05:59.292 --> 06:00.459
<i> ♪ Wait! This is my thing! ♪</i>

06:00.561 --> 06:02.093
<i> ♪ A better way to be bad ♪</i>

06:02.195 --> 06:03.628
<i> ♪ You shall do as I command ♪</i>

06:03.730 --> 06:05.063
<i> ♪ I will rule this triad ♪</i>

06:05.165 --> 06:06.565
<i> ♪ Hey! This is my song. ♪</i>

06:06.667 --> 06:10.201
<i> ♪ Sorry not any long-er! ♪</i>

06:10.303 --> 06:11.970
<i> ♪ A better way to be bad ♪</i>

06:12.072 --> 06:13.371
<i> ♪ Now you're making me mad ♪</i>

06:13.473 --> 06:14.939
<i> ♪ Won't the ponies be sad ♪</i>

06:15.041 --> 06:16.375
<i> ♪ That would make me so glad. ♪</i>

06:16.477 --> 06:21.546
<i> ♪ Now we got a better</i>
<i> way to be bad! ♪</i>

06:25.452 --> 06:27.686
Hey! You stepped on my cue!

06:27.788 --> 06:29.788
Well, I did not!
Ah.. your rhythm was way off.

06:32.059 --> 06:33.592
ENOUGH!

06:34.762 --> 06:35.862
I had hoped by now

06:35.963 --> 06:37.763
you would have resolved
your differences.

06:37.865 --> 06:39.798
But apparently not.

06:39.900 --> 06:42.734
Perhaps if we knew
what the plan WAS,

06:42.836 --> 06:45.170
we would be better
able to prepare.

06:45.472 --> 06:47.839
Assuming you even have a plan.

06:47.941 --> 06:50.075
Of course, I have a plan.

06:50.477 --> 06:52.644
I have located an
object of power

06:52.746 --> 06:55.547
and it occurs to me this
is the perfect test.

06:55.849 --> 06:58.384
The three of you will work
together to retrieve it.

06:58.886 --> 07:04.089
Against this item, those
ponies won't stand a chance.

07:04.791 --> 07:09.094
I have come close to ruling
Equestria several times.

07:09.296 --> 07:11.330
Perhaps I should be
the one to lead us.

07:11.532 --> 07:13.965
I nearly drained all the
magic from Equestria!

07:14.067 --> 07:15.334
That was good!

07:15.436 --> 07:19.604
<i>I absorbed</i> all the
magic of Equestria!

07:19.706 --> 07:23.975
I could feel it flowing
through my body as I grew!

07:29.616 --> 07:31.516
Each of you FAILED to defeat

07:31.618 --> 07:33.786
Twilight Sparkle
and her friends.

07:34.888 --> 07:38.390
My power is greater than
all of yours combined.

07:38.492 --> 07:41.560
This is but a fraction
of it. Understood?

07:41.762 --> 07:43.628
Uh huh. OK!

07:45.399 --> 07:48.500
Now YOU shall retrieve
the rest of it.

07:49.302 --> 07:52.871
<i> ♪ [mysterious music] ♪</i>

07:52.973 --> 07:55.140
<i> Thousands of moons ago,</i>

07:55.342 --> 07:58.143
<i> the self-righteous</i>
<i> Gusty the Great,</i>

07:58.245 --> 08:00.679
<i> unable to best me</i>
<i> face-to-face,</i>

08:00.781 --> 08:02.948
<i> stole my bewitching bell,</i>

08:03.350 --> 08:06.151
<i> a talisman containing</i>
<i>  much of my own magic. </i>

08:06.453 --> 08:08.887
<i> The bell cannot be destroyed</i>

08:09.089 --> 08:11.056
<i> so Gusty hid it in a place</i>

08:11.158 --> 08:13.992
<i> it has taken me</i>
<i> millennia to discover.</i>

08:14.194 --> 08:17.462
<i> An enchanted cave</i>
<i> high atop Mt. Everhoof</i>

08:17.564 --> 08:20.866
<i> protected by magical</i>
<i> winds that prevent anypony</i>

08:20.968 --> 08:22.401
<i> from reaching its peak.</i>

08:22.703 --> 08:27.406
<i> There the bell has</i>
<i> remained... until now.</i>

08:27.908 --> 08:32.311
Scale Mt. Everhoof.
Bring me back my bell.

08:32.713 --> 08:36.315
Ha ha! The ease of this
task is laughable.

08:39.152 --> 08:40.919
Well, it sounded easy.

08:44.504 --> 08:48.504
♪♪

08:48.629 --> 08:50.128
Scale the mountain.

08:50.230 --> 08:52.030
Retrieve Grogar's bell.

08:52.232 --> 08:54.833
Together! I drew
up a detailed plan

08:54.935 --> 08:57.136
with several visual
aides to show how we can...

08:57.938 --> 08:59.905
ditch each other
and do it alone.

09:00.007 --> 09:01.906
Maybe when I'm waiting
for them at the top,

09:02.008 --> 09:03.675
then they'll appreciate me.

09:11.017 --> 09:14.753
<i> ♪ [music intensifies] ♪</i>

09:14.855 --> 09:24.963
♪♪

09:28.135 --> 09:31.903
As if anything on this
mountain is scarier than I.

09:32.005 --> 09:33.404
Ha ha ha ha!

09:33.506 --> 09:39.744
♪♪

09:41.915 --> 09:42.647
Ptui!

09:48.021 --> 09:51.256
Halt! Who goes there? A pony!?

09:51.358 --> 09:53.091
There ain't been
ponies round here in

09:53.193 --> 09:55.360
I-don't-know-how-many moons!

09:58.865 --> 10:00.499
Oh, golly, good sir.

10:00.601 --> 10:03.769
I'm just a poor lost
pony looking for help.

10:04.471 --> 10:06.405
Oh, don't fret li'l filly.

10:06.607 --> 10:09.508
Ol' Rusty Bucket
here, at yer service!

10:09.710 --> 10:11.876
I'm so glad
I found you!

10:12.078 --> 10:14.647
I need help getting to
the top of the mountain.

10:14.949 --> 10:17.182
Eh. No can do, ma'am.

10:18.251 --> 10:19.450
WHY NOT!?

10:20.388 --> 10:25.223
Shh! Not so loud! This here's
avalanche territory!

10:25.425 --> 10:27.358
I'm the guardian of
this here mountain.

10:27.460 --> 10:30.161
It's my job to keep
ponies from heading up.

10:30.263 --> 10:32.497
Nothing at the top
but dangerous snow,

10:32.599 --> 10:34.966
dangerous ice, and
dangerous wind.

10:35.168 --> 10:37.436
Basically, it's dangerous.

10:38.238 --> 10:40.972
It must get lonely
all by yourself.

10:41.074 --> 10:43.442
Maybe I could be
your... friend?

10:43.544 --> 10:45.610
Oh! I'd love a friend!

10:46.012 --> 10:47.879
So now that we
are friends,

10:47.981 --> 10:49.782
you could help me
up the mountain.

10:50.684 --> 10:53.618
Hm. A real friend wouldn't
ask me to do something

10:53.720 --> 10:55.320
I'm not supposed to do.

10:55.422 --> 10:57.956
Says so right here in the
journal of friendship

10:58.058 --> 11:00.959
written by Twilight
Sparkle and <i>her</i> friends.

11:01.761 --> 11:04.595
ARE! YOU! KIDDING ME!

11:08.268 --> 11:09.435
Sshhhhhhh!

11:10.437 --> 11:12.070
I didn't want to
be friends anyway.

11:12.272 --> 11:13.204
Aww...

11:20.547 --> 11:22.847
♪♪

11:24.051 --> 11:31.256
♪♪

11:31.358 --> 11:32.857
Almost there.

11:32.959 --> 11:46.171
♪♪

11:48.975 --> 11:55.580
♪♪

11:55.682 --> 11:57.416
Nope. Not that
way neither.

12:08.929 --> 12:10.729
I TRIED being NICE.

12:12.732 --> 12:16.301
Shhhhh. Now just calm
down there, filly.

12:16.403 --> 12:17.370
You calm down!

12:17.571 --> 12:21.238
Ponies are supposed to
do what I ask them to do!

12:21.341 --> 12:23.908
It's like MY thing, OK?

12:31.651 --> 12:32.317
Eh.

12:34.387 --> 12:37.889
♪♪

12:37.991 --> 12:41.492
Apparently I don't
need anypony else.

12:42.594 --> 12:49.934
♪♪

13:03.850 --> 13:05.850
It's not. Funny. Tirek!

13:06.252 --> 13:10.855
Didn't make it to the
top? Surprise surprise.

13:10.957 --> 13:13.024
You didn't make it
to the top either!

13:13.226 --> 13:15.827
I didn't try to...

13:16.029 --> 13:16.595
What!?

13:16.697 --> 13:18.863
It took about five
minutes to deduce

13:18.965 --> 13:20.565
that Grogar was right.

13:20.667 --> 13:22.834
None of us could
make it up alone.

13:22.936 --> 13:25.737
So rather than subject
myself to the elements,

13:25.839 --> 13:29.607
I decided to let you
two face the danger,

13:29.709 --> 13:33.444
take what you learned and
use it to my advantage.

13:34.915 --> 13:37.348
I put up with your "I'm
smarter than you" attitude

13:37.450 --> 13:39.618
in Tartarus! But
I'm over it!

13:40.220 --> 13:42.453
I've had enough of you
trying to manipulate me

13:42.555 --> 13:45.490
with that insincere
syrupy sweetness.

13:45.592 --> 13:48.193
At least now we can
see the real you.

13:48.495 --> 13:52.297
This is NOT the real me!
I'm cute and LOVABLE!

13:52.599 --> 13:58.369
Ha! No, you're not. You're
annoying and you snore!

13:58.471 --> 14:00.104
I do not snore!

14:03.176 --> 14:06.444
At least I don't talk to
my gram-gram in <i>my</i> sleep.

14:06.546 --> 14:09.113
Don't you DARE bring
Gram-Gram into this!

14:11.584 --> 14:12.751
This is your fault!

14:22.595 --> 14:23.428
Mmm?

14:24.230 --> 14:26.965
♪♪

14:27.067 --> 14:28.866
Quick! It's
distracted! Let's go!

14:28.968 --> 14:29.667
Wait.

14:38.945 --> 14:41.880
Mmmm. So much love...!

14:42.082 --> 14:45.050
I haven't eaten
this well in <i>ages</i>.

14:45.652 --> 14:47.586
[gag] So gross...

14:48.088 --> 14:49.721
Just so we're clear.

14:49.923 --> 14:51.890
I didn't save you
because I like you.

14:51.992 --> 14:53.858
I did it because...
Because I...

14:53.960 --> 14:56.060
Neeeeeed us?

14:56.362 --> 14:57.262
...Yes.

14:57.664 --> 15:00.064
Clearly, I was
right to wait.

15:00.466 --> 15:03.134
Now tell me everything
you learned today.

15:03.236 --> 15:04.502
Leave nothing out.

15:04.604 --> 15:09.908
♪♪

15:10.010 --> 15:11.275
Why are you doing that?

15:11.377 --> 15:13.378
Didn't you already
drain it of love?

15:13.480 --> 15:16.014
I always save a little
for the next day.

15:16.216 --> 15:19.050
You cocoon all of
your... meals?

15:19.152 --> 15:20.102
Of course.

15:20.303 --> 15:22.553
So when you pony-napped
Twilight and the others,

15:22.655 --> 15:23.855
you cocooned them.

15:24.057 --> 15:27.358
Yes. Until that sow
Starlight Glimmer

15:27.460 --> 15:31.396
freed them, corrupted my
subjects, and stole my hive!

15:31.698 --> 15:33.598
Those ponies have weaknesses.

15:33.700 --> 15:36.167
I used that turncoat Discord.

15:36.269 --> 15:38.569
Tricked him into
helping me capture his

15:38.671 --> 15:40.705
so called "friends".

15:40.807 --> 15:45.276
Ah. Discord was really something
until friendship ruined him.

15:45.578 --> 15:47.678
You should've seen
Twilight's face

15:47.780 --> 15:50.515
when her friends appeared
in bubbles around me.

15:50.617 --> 15:51.349
She was all...

15:58.158 --> 16:00.558
She's SO stressed
out all the time!

16:00.660 --> 16:03.327
When I posed as her
former foal-sitter,

16:03.429 --> 16:05.696
I thought she was
going to implode!

16:08.901 --> 16:10.234
I wish I could
have seen her face

16:10.336 --> 16:13.471
when I nearly erased all
the magic from Equestria...

16:13.573 --> 16:17.375
ALL magic was a little
excessive, don't you think?

16:17.477 --> 16:18.609
Meh. I think big.

16:18.711 --> 16:21.079
Besides, it would've
been worth it

16:21.181 --> 16:24.916
just to see Twilight and
her friends bow down to ME.

16:25.018 --> 16:28.686
Indeed, it would. Who
wouldn't love to see

16:28.788 --> 16:32.490
those prissy ponies realize
they've lost everything!

16:33.793 --> 16:36.260
I'm a pathetic pony princess!

16:36.362 --> 16:40.665
I made a detailed list of
all the ways I'm a failure!

16:44.704 --> 16:46.737
You know, working with you two

16:46.839 --> 16:49.074
may not be the worst thing.

16:49.576 --> 16:52.143
Mm. Perhaps... as long as it results

16:52.245 --> 16:54.813
in the complete
destruction of our enemies.

16:55.015 --> 16:57.548
I wouldn't have
it any other way.

16:57.650 --> 16:59.450
Do the "pathetic
princess" thing again!

17:17.069 --> 17:18.202
I'm OK!

17:18.304 --> 17:26.911
♪♪

17:28.748 --> 18:01.623
♪♪

18:05.618 --> 18:06.951
[zap] Wah!

18:09.689 --> 18:10.789
[zap] Uh!

18:11.491 --> 18:13.558
Can you absorb it
and make it go away?

18:13.660 --> 18:16.695
I can only absorb magic
from living beings.

18:17.597 --> 18:18.763
Like her..?

18:19.665 --> 18:20.698
Betrayal!

18:21.200 --> 18:23.201
Not betrayal. Teamwork.

18:23.403 --> 18:25.269
If Tirek absorbs your energy,

18:25.371 --> 18:27.638
he might be strong
enough to break through.

18:27.740 --> 18:29.073
And then..?

18:29.175 --> 18:31.109
Then... he
gives it back.

18:31.711 --> 18:32.543
I do?

18:32.645 --> 18:33.412
Mhm!

18:34.013 --> 18:36.880
How do I know you won't
take my magic and leave me?

18:36.983 --> 18:39.218
Would we do
that to you?

18:40.220 --> 18:42.353
OK. Normally
yes, we would.

18:42.655 --> 18:45.389
I'll give you
your magic back...

18:46.326 --> 18:47.325
Do it.

18:55.201 --> 18:59.804
So. Much. Power!

19:01.374 --> 19:03.541
Welcome back, baby!

19:05.278 --> 19:07.178
It's not big enough for me!

19:07.480 --> 19:08.714
Maybe not you.

19:09.816 --> 19:12.984
Keep it open or I'll
be trapped forever!

19:14.086 --> 19:16.220
Would that be so terrible?

19:19.459 --> 19:23.494
Can't... hold.... much longer!

19:24.797 --> 19:26.464
HURRY!

19:30.102 --> 19:31.036
Ta-da!

19:31.938 --> 19:33.071
My magic...

19:41.314 --> 19:44.315
I... wasn't sure you were
going to give it back.

19:44.617 --> 19:47.618
Neither was I. But working
together seemed...

19:47.720 --> 19:50.555
smarter than to
continue fighting.

19:50.757 --> 19:53.391
When we helped each other,
it felt better somehow.

19:53.493 --> 19:57.328
I haven't felt like this
since before I lost my hive.

19:57.430 --> 19:59.630
Having others who will
be there for you...

19:59.732 --> 20:01.666
is pleasing.

20:02.068 --> 20:07.171
All of these years...
taking power from ponies.

20:07.373 --> 20:09.907
When you use your
power to help others...

20:10.109 --> 20:11.443
Yes.... it feels....

20:12.445 --> 20:14.144
NO!

20:14.246 --> 20:14.979
Whoa!

20:15.881 --> 20:19.217
The magic of <i>friendship</i>
is like a disease.

20:19.319 --> 20:21.953
An infection that spreads
to those around you!

20:22.255 --> 20:24.322
I watched it
infect my hive.

20:24.424 --> 20:26.390
I will NOT let it get ME!

20:26.692 --> 20:27.258
Same!

20:27.360 --> 20:28.459
Obviously.

20:28.761 --> 20:31.996
But... Grogar said we
have to work together.

20:32.198 --> 20:34.432
Grogar is too powerful.

20:34.534 --> 20:36.901
Something must be
done about that...

20:37.603 --> 20:41.105
Let Grogar think we're
his loyal servants.

20:41.207 --> 20:45.043
In the meantime, we'll
hatch our own plan.

20:45.145 --> 20:48.579
Ooo. I love a good
backstabbing!

20:48.981 --> 20:50.414
After that, we can go back

20:50.516 --> 20:52.883
to trying to..
destroy each other.

20:52.985 --> 20:55.453
In the meantime, what
do we do with this?

20:57.190 --> 21:00.258
You failed to
retrieve the BELL?

21:00.860 --> 21:03.427
We're sorry,
Almighty Grogar.

21:03.529 --> 21:05.997
We worked together
as you asked!

21:06.099 --> 21:08.599
We just aren't as
powerful as you!

21:13.606 --> 21:14.806
Obviously!

21:15.208 --> 21:17.108
At least you finally
did as you were told

21:17.210 --> 21:18.609
and worked together.

21:19.946 --> 21:20.979
Of course!

21:21.281 --> 21:22.847
Whatever you command.

21:22.949 --> 21:24.849
Forget about
that old bell.

21:24.951 --> 21:25.719
You were right!

21:25.820 --> 21:29.888
We're SO much more powerful
when we work as a team...
